HEADWORD: Langrel
<hw>Lan"grel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of shot formerly used at sea for
tearing sails and rigging. It consisted of bolts, nails, and other
pieces of iron fastened together or inclosed in a canister.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

